    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka says talks with IMF resumed, debt advisors doing analysis",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has resumed discussion with the International Monetary Fund on final policy issues and debt advisors are continuing analytical work needed for re-structuring, the Finance Ministry said.",
        "Sri Lanka has a stable government to continue negotiations with the IMF, the President\u2019s media office said. Sri Lanka expects to successfully conclude negotiations, the statement said.",
        "The Finance Ministry said protests and changes in administration delayed the process.",
        "\u201cHowever with the formation of the new government, technical discussions between the Sri Lankan authorities and the IMF have now resumed with a view to finalizing the few remaining policy matters that need to agreed upon prior to reaching the a [staff level agreement]\u201d the statement said.",
        "\u201cThe Advisors have made considerable progress in the analytical framework for debt operation, prior to formal engagement with Sri Lanka creditors,\u201d the statement said.",
        "\u201cThe government is committed to engaging its creditors in good faith with a view to reaching a comprehensive debt restructuring program that provides a far and sustainable outcome for all stakeholders.\u201d"
      ],
